{"key":"post-17203439","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17203439</id>\n<content>Another option is to place the needle on the syringe and boil in a pot of water with a lid for 20 minutes or so.&amp;nbsp; Then pull boiling water into the syringe and expel it several times. Then drop the syringe back in the boiling water, put the lid on and take into your lab.&amp;nbsp; Leave the lid on the pot until ready to use the syringe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As always, don't forget to flame sterilize the needle before the first jar and between each jar after that to prevent cross-contamination.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17203523</next>\n<prev>17203383</prev>\n<first>17202759</first>\n<last>17203766</last>\n<when>1352690143</when>\n<utime>11/12/12 05:15 AM</utime>\n</post>"}